---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
import img1 from '../../assets/Audio_Equalizer.png';

const projectSpecs = [
  { label: "Location", value: "Purdue University" },
  { label: "Dates", value: "April 2024" },
  { label: "Course", value: "ECE 20007 Linear Circuit Analysis Lab" },
  { label: "Skills", value: "Circuit Analysis, Basic Circuit Design, LT Spice" }
];
---

<ProjectLayout 
    title="Analog Audio Equalizer "
    subtitle="Coursework in Linear Circuit Analysis"
    images={[img1]}
    specs={projectSpecs}>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
        The final project for this course challenged my knowledge in circuit design and implementation. 
        The goal: build a functioning analog audio equalizer. 
    </p> 

    <p>
        This project utilized analog RC band pass and RCL band reject filters to create the bass, treble, 
        and mid-range channels, each with -3dB cutoffs. These channels could have their gain controlled by 
        three potentiometers to achieve the desired mix. Further, a master volume control potentiometer was 
        added to control the entire device. The equalizer was required to output less than 15 mV(RMS) at 
        minimum power and near 100 mV(RMS) at maximum power. Additionally, the maximum recombined signal 
        could not ripple more than 15 mV(RMS) and the entire device needed to output more than 400 mW of 
        power across all desired frequencies. 
    </p>
    <section>
        <div class="video-frame">
            <video 
              controls
              src="../../Equalizer.mp4"
              preload="metadata"
              poster="../../Equalizer_Placeholder.png"
              class="film-glow"
              >
              Your browser does not support the video tag.
            </video>
        </div>
    </section>
</ProjectLayout>



<style is:global>
    .video-frame {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: #000; /* Mimics the dark theater behind the screen */
        padding: 10px; /* Creates a small "letterbox" frame */
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        transition: border-color 0.4s ease, box-shadow 0.4s ease;
    }

    .video-frame:hover {
        border-color: var(--accent-orange);
        box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--accent-glow);
    }
    
    .project-hero-img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 600px;
    }

    h2 {
        margin-top: -0.8rem;
    }

    video.film-glow {
        width: 100%;
        display: block;
        border-radius: 4px;
        /* Cinematic color grade: slight contrast boost */
        filter: contrast(1.1) saturate(0.9);
    }
</style>